x4freetext: The targets were self-supporting foils made from
separated chromium isotopes. The targets were
less than 200 mu-g/cm2 thick, corresponding to an
energy loss of less than 10 keV for 10 MeV deuterons.
Rotatable lid on which were mounted
two silicon surface barrier counters. E-detector was
0.2 cm thick, dE - detector was 0.010 cm thick.

x4freetext: The statistical errors and the error due to
the 0.2 degr. uncertainty in the scattering angle gave
a total error in the measurement of the differential
cross-section having a maximum value of 4% at 20.degr.
and decreasing with angle to less than 1.5% at angles
greater than 70. degr. In all the measurements the
